{
  "texts": [
    "Regularized MLE only generates notably more unique active molecules when using the top current replay buffer, compared to A2C and PPO using the same replay buffer.",
    "When using PPO and A2C, the replay buffers All current and Bin current yield the largest number of active molecules.",
    "Moreover, when using Regularized MLE, utilizing All current generates the largest number, whereas Top current is the second-best replay buffer.",
    "As seen in Fig. 5b, Regularized MLE utilizing All current show the largest median of (unique) active scaffolds with low variability, compared to A2C and PPO.",
    "This combination also shows the largest median of generated (unique) active topological scaffolds, as seen in Fig. 5c."
  ]
}